    "We identified only two studies that explicitly discussed regulatory issues.",
    "In the study by Bahamazava and Nanda (2022), after discovering the preferred methods of buying cryptocurrencies for money laundering, they cross-examined anti-money laundering regulations in Italy and Russia to see if they have corresponding paragraphs to address such purchasing methods.",
